A man was arrested after he was found with stolen railway metal worth about R300 000. Pietermaritzburg police spokesperson, Sergeant Mthokozisi Ngobese, told The Witness that on Tuesday an intelligence driven operation led by the uMgungundlovu crime intelligence members with role players from the municipality, Eskom, Telkom, Transnet and Mountain Rise Crime Prevention helped recover railway items belonging to the Msunduzi Municipality. He said the items were seized from a second-hand scrap dealer. He said the man was arrested and charged with being in possession of suspected stolen property. He is expected to appear at the Pietermaritzburg Magistrate’s court soon.